<br>
One factor that certianly comes into play is burn out.  Not burn out from 'oh, I do too many quests', but from the 'I try to run a nice quest and some darn L60's come in and ruin it everytime'.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, if you want quests, get online during an adventure weekend.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I stumbled into 4 GM events in 3 days over Haloween. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umomur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Momur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 271<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/3/02 4:21:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2277.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: GM Events</span><hr size=1> Somehow I managed to miss all of the Halloween stuff. But other than that the GM events I've seen are a complete waste of time.<br>
<br>
GM takes control of a big dragon, does not respond to hails, kills a bunch of people, eventually decides it's time to die. Only Uber High level folks have a chance and nothing drops. <br>
<br>
GM plops a pile of Drolvargs in DL and names himself a Drolvarg Warlord. Wow, so exciting. <br>
<br>
There are sooooo many ways to make a decent event that does not require mindless killing and could get many people involved. I do not know why VI doesn't even bother.<br>
<br>
- How about a scavenger hunt?<br>
- How about a level restricted PvP/Duel best of the best type event? Announce in a zone and whoever is there at the time can participate.<br>
- How about a group based event, like, take your full group and recover these 6 items from mobs then return to me for reward? First full group to return gets something or whatever.<br>
- Save a princess from a tower - GM could hand out an item that must be delivered to the princess in that way it can be restricted by level.<br>
- Assassinate an NPC in a city.<br>
<br>
Jeez, use a little imagination.<br>
